						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in the Liṅgāyata-<hi rend="italic">maṭha.</hi></p>						

						<p>Veṅkaṭapatirāya, 1542 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 4565, Chitrabhānu, Āśvija śu. 5.</hi> The Śaka year given is obviously a mistake for 1465, The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds to <hi rend="bold">1542 A.D., September 14.</hi> The Śaka year would be current.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift to a deity, probably by Immaḍi Chikarāya, son of Chikarāya-Tammaya-gauḍa of Sugaṭūru for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
